Package lshfindex

Class LSHFPrefixTree

java.lang.Object
lshfindex.LSHFPrefixTree
public class LSHFPrefixTree extends Object
LSHFPrefixTree implements a prefix tree for the LSH-Forest. It uses the btree package template: internal (index) pages hold <key, PageID> pairs and leaf pages hold <key, RID> pairs. For simplicity, this implementation starts with a single leaf page (i.e. no internal nodes) and does not implement full node splitting. The tree supports insertion, scanning all entries, range search, and nearest neighbor search.

      public void insert(Vector100DKey key, RID rid) throws Exception
      Inserts a <key, RID> pair into the prefix tree. For this simple implementation, we assume the tree contains only a single leaf page. In a complete implementation, this method would traverse internal nodes and handle splits.
      Parameters:
      key - the Vector100DKey (hash value) to insert.
      rid - the RID corresponding to the data record.
      Throws:
      Exception - if insertion fails.
